## summon

### Instructions


You have these skills at your disposal, when it is clear they can help you solve a problem or you are asked to use them:
• bugfix - One-shot bug fix: investigate → fix → test → commit → push → PR. Designed for the daily fix-and-ship cycle across Rust, Go, Python, SvelteKit, and Node projects.
• ci-fix - Fix CI failures: reads errors from local checks or GitHub Actions, fixes them, and iterates until CI is green. Works across SvelteKit, Rust, Go, Python, and Node projects.
• corpo - Personal health assistant that indexes and searches your nutritional programs, training plans, supplement cycles, and body composition history so Claude can answer questions, cross-reference data, and provide health guidance within any conversation. Reads numbered program PDFs (#16–#XX), Garmin wearable exports, and bloodwork results to build a searchable health knowledge base. Tracks body composition trends (weight, fat mass, lean mass, BMI), manages supplement/compound cycling with health risk assessment, calculates daily macros and calorie intake, and maintains persistent memory of next steps, nutritionist recommendations, and decisions between sessions. Use this skill whenever the user asks about their health data, nutrition programs, supplement history, weight trends, body composition analysis, training program comparisons, health risk assessment from supplement use, wants predictions based on their program history, or asks Claude to remember/recall health-related information. Trigger on mentions of: programmi, programma, nutrizionista, integratori, supplementi, peso, massa grassa, massa magra, composizione corporea, cutting, bulking, SARM, PCT, pro-ormone, ciclo, allenamento, dieta, piano alimentare, calorie, kcal, macros, proteine, carboidrati, grassi, macronutrienti, deficit calorico, surplus, Garmin, analisi del sangue, esami, Musolino, or any reference to numbered programs (#XX). Also trigger when the user uploads PDF files with nutritional/training data, Garmin export data, or asks for health risk analysis related to performance-enhancing compounds.
• email-tone - Rewrite raw content as an email using your personal email tone of voice. Usage: /email-tone <paste your raw content or prompt>
• git-cleanup - Clean up git history: squash fixup commits, reword messages per conventional commits, and present a clean commit log. One-shot command for the rebase-squash-reword cycle.
• goose-doc-guide - Reference goose documentation to create, configure, or explain goose-specific features like recipes, extensions, sessions, and providers. You MUST fetch relevant goose docs before answering. You MUST NOT rely on training data or assumptions for any goose-specific fields, values, names, syntax, or commands.
• issue-analyze - Deep issue investigation: analyze a GitHub issue or bug report, trace the root cause, check spec compliance, and produce a structured report. Read-only — does not modify code.
• me-setup - Build your personal tone-of-voice profile by analyzing your real writing from connected sources. Usage: /me-setup <instructions on where to find your writing — e.g., 'check my sent emails, my GitHub repos, and my Google Docs'>
• nutrizionista-analyzer - Personal health assistant that indexes and searches your nutritional programs, training plans, supplement cycles, and body composition history so Claude can answer questions, cross-reference data, and provide health guidance within any conversation. Reads numbered program PDFs (#16–#XX), Garmin wearable exports, and bloodwork results to build a searchable health knowledge base. Tracks body composition trends (weight, fat mass, lean mass, BMI), manages supplement/compound cycling with health risk assessment, calculates daily macros and calorie intake, and maintains persistent memory of next steps, nutritionist recommendations, and decisions between sessions. Use this skill whenever the user asks about their health data, nutrition programs, supplement history, weight trends, body composition analysis, training program comparisons, health risk assessment from supplement use, wants predictions based on their program history, or asks Claude to remember/recall health-related information. Trigger on mentions of: programmi, programma, nutrizionista, integratori, supplementi, peso, massa grassa, massa magra, composizione corporea, cutting, bulking, SARM, PCT, pro-ormone, ciclo, allenamento, dieta, piano alimentare, calorie, kcal, macros, proteine, carboidrati, grassi, macronutrienti, deficit calorico, surplus, Garmin, analisi del sangue, esami, Musolino, or any reference to numbered programs (#XX). Also trigger when the user uploads PDF files with nutritional/training data, Garmin export data, or asks for health risk analysis related to performance-enhancing compounds.
• pr-status - Fetch and triage unresolved PR review comments: categorize by severity and confidence, show what needs fixing vs what to defer, and present a structured action plan.
• review-and-pr - Review all current changes for production safety, fix any problems found, iterate until 110% confident, then open a PR and wait for CI to pass. Use after you already have changes ready.
• review-feedback - Address PR review comments: read reviewer feedback from GitHub, apply fixes, run CI, push, and reply to each comment thread. One-shot command for the review-fix-push cycle.
• review-pr - Review an incoming PR: fetch the diff, perform a structured code review with severity labels, and post review comments. Uses the project owner's direct, ACK-based tone of voice.
• ship - Full feature lifecycle: implement, verify CI, commit, push, create PR, and monitor remote CI until green. Works across SvelteKit, Rust, Go, Python, and Node projects.
• write-tone - Rewrite raw content using your personal writing tone of voice. Usage: /write-tone <paste your raw content>
If the user's message starts with /<skill-name> and matches one of these skills, treat that as an explicit request to use the matching skill. Any text after the skill name is the user's task.
